@startuml
' @id(DOM-FONT-DATABASE)
' @id(DOM-OCL-VIEW)
' @id(DOM-PUML-SOURCE-VIEW)
' @desc(DOM-FONT-DATABASE, "Implemented: usvg::fontdb::Database built once by shared_fontdb() and Arc-cloned into usvg::Options at every parse site.")
' @desc(DOM-OCL-VIEW, "Implemented as mdd-viewer OclView { sub_mode: OclSubMode, loaded, source, page }: state for a selected .ocl file — Source paints raw text, Diagram paints the synthesized constraints SVG.")
' @desc(DOM-PUML-SOURCE-VIEW, "Implemented as mdd-viewer SourceView { loaded: Option<String>, source: String }: state behind the CentralPanel Source toggle. When self.view == View::Source, MddViewer::source_ui reads the selected model file once (cached by loaded) and paints `source` read-only; it touches no DiagramPage / rasterizer.")
' Current-side viewer domain: the font database the SVG rasterizer
' depends on (populated by shared_fontdb), the OCL-view state, and the
' PlantUML Source-view state behind the Diagram | Source | Diff toggle.
title Viewer domain — font database + OCL view + PlantUML source (current)

enum OclSubMode {
  Source
  Diagram
}

class SvgRasterizer {
  + parse_intrinsic_size(bytes) : Vec2
  + rebuild(ctx, zoom) : Result
}

class FontDatabase {
  + fontCount : int
  + defaultFamily : String
  + loadSystemFonts() : void
}

class OclView {
  + sub_mode : OclSubMode
  + loaded : Option<String>
  + source : String
  + page : Option<DiagramPage>
}

class SourceView {
  + loaded : Option<String>
  + source : String
}

SvgRasterizer "1" o-- "1" FontDatabase : resolves <text> via >
OclView --> OclSubMode

note bottom of FontDatabase
  Backed by usvg::fontdb::Database. Built once
  in shared_fontdb() (static OnceLock), filled
  by load_system_fonts(), then Arc-cloned into
  usvg::Options.fontdb at every parse site.
end note

note bottom of OclView
  MddViewer::ocl_ui: Source paints `source`
  (read-only, @id/context/inv colored); Diagram
  loads Project::rendered_svg_path(.ocl) via
  DiagramPage and paints it with paint_canvas,
  else a placeholder (OCL-OCL-VIEW-SUBMODE,
  OCL-OCL-DIAGRAM-NEEDS-RENDER).
end note

note bottom of SourceView
  MddViewer::source_ui (View::Source branch):
  reads the selected model file once into
  `source` (cached by `loaded`) and paints it in
  egui::ScrollArea::both as read-only monospace,
  highlighting `' @` markers, `@start`/`@end`
  directives and `'` comments. No DiagramPage or
  rasterizer call, so it needs no rendered SVG
  (OCL-PUML-SOURCE-NO-RENDER).
end note
@enduml
